---
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never try and start a dev environment
- The app runs on port 4900 (not 3000). Always use localhost:4900 for API calls and URLs
- Never check the app with curl commands
- Never run `npm run dev`
- Assume localhost:4900 is already running. Ask the user to restart if needed. Never manage the server yourself
- Check prompt guides in the docs or call the SQLite DB to get prompting context for image generation
- Prompts need to be between 400 and 500 tokens, (~350 words)
- When generating images, do not return excessive descriptions of the images that were generated. 
-- The images themselves are being shown to the user and we do not need an explanation. 
-- Return short responses after the images are complete efficient use of bullets
- when creating a video, always include the script in the prompt. the prompt is the only way to control the video.
- Don't summarize the chat unless we have as very very long chat. you're doing that too much so just don't do it. 